Diagram Used in the Project
(Use Case Diagram)
1- What is a Use Case Diagram?

A Use Case Diagram is a type of UML (Unified Modeling Language) diagram used to:

Represent system functionalities

Show how users (actors) interact with the system

Describe system behavior from the user’s perspective

2- Diagram Used in This Project

In this project, we used a Use Case Diagram to model:

Attendance System

Library System

To-Do List System

All systems were connected and included <<include>> and <<extend>> relationships.

3- Actors

Teacher / Staff

Student

Librarian

User

4- Relationships Used

<<include>> → Mandatory functionality

<<extend>> → Optional or conditional functionality

Example:

Mark Attendance <<include>> Login

Edit Attendance <<extend>> View Attendance
